<br>
Original post dated 2/12/02 4:55:07 pm:<br>
<br>
I think your flame is rather mild Laurri. Frankly I am unimpressed. I expected much more from you (shakes his head). If your flame were compared to hot sauce it would definitely not rank up there with El Chinga Tu Madre (TM) Brand Dip and Tarnish Remover... It's more of a sub-standard Taco Bell mild sauce type of flame. If it's one skill a good guild leader needs its flaming ability! So allow me to assist you in brushing up on your skill. <br>
<br>
So here is my guide to the ultimate burn. Now, on to the lesson, take notes, there will be a quiz at the end of the lesson:<br>
<br>
1) Profanity: Every 3rd or 4th word of each sentence should be some form of “curse” word. Alternatively you can leave the majority of a sentence cuss-free and just rely on a single “slam dunk” phrase like donkey-raping @#%$-eater, tuft of rectal pubic-hair, or festering blob of sputum floating in the toilet bowl of life. On top of that you score extra points if you can form an entire sentence with nothing but profanity. However it must be creative otherwise you just make yourself look like a low-brow Jersey construction worker who should have been wearing steel-toed boots when that cinder block landed on his foot.<br>
<br>
2) The Underlying Burn: This should be related to things everyone already knows about the target. It is main reason for the flame expressed in mocking tones. This is the core of the flame and you cannot do without it. Example: So you think we are not uber enough eh? Well I hope Magna Vitae can satisfy your need for uberness. Think of us while you are raiding crushbone. And don't forget to pull your head out of your ass and say hello every once in a while, cause it's a huge boost to our moral whenever you stop by and allow us to mock your complete inability to form a coherent sentence. I nearly crapped my pants I was laughing so hard at your unintelligible post on The Blast Furnace.<br>
<br>
3) The Quote: The Quote is an essential part of every flame. It allows you to kick the target right in the berries. Here’s a little example quote by our friend Punkrawk Bob:<br>
Quote:<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
This guy is a @#%$ little bitch, someone needs to kick his ass so he'll wake up from his dillusions of him mattering.<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Well, where to start? First of all Punkrawk obviously needs to go back to 3rd grade and study English grammar. I mean a good elementary school education could mean the difference between a job scrubbing toilets at Burger King and a job cooking fries at McDonalds. If it’s too hard for ol’ Punko here he shouldn’t be too hard on himself though, most of those fast food joints have pictures on the cash registers now so he can just point at the food I’m ordering. But Punk, if you’re out there, you’d better not put any @#%$ pickles on my hamburger cause I HATE pickles.<br>
<br>
4) The Free-Side-Order Burn (A.K.A. ‘The Churro’): This should be a bit of history about the person in question, perhaps some information that not everyone was privy to beforehand. Extra points are scored if the target didn't expect you to sink low enough to make this information public knowledge.<br>
<br>
5) The ASCII burn: Where would flames be without the American Standard Code for Information Interchange. With it you can attempt wonderful pictures of yourself 'burning' the target like so:<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
      me                                         Meak<br>
