<br>
I'd have to say that the best flames usually come out when Gharbad hits his last nerve and gets extremely pissed off, like in some of the Brell's Threads.  There are quite a few others that are extremely funny, too, but those come to mind at the moment.  <br>
<br>
But I have to admit, I think any thread that TWC plays defendant in gets my vote for the most entertaining.  I just can't say enough about Seani's ability to let fly with worthless cross-analysis, pointless information, and so many invalid points that it puts even Johnny Cochrane to shame. Sometimes I even find myself wondering if the cases that Seani and Co. present are actually cover-ups, or if they really believe their own bullshit.  Whatever the case may be, 9 times out of 10 it leads to some pretty damn good reading.  <br>
